Is there a way to pull _just_ the MSP ID from the byte array returned from `getCreator()`? I've implemented the following, which works, but I'm not positive it's a good idea:

```
private static String getSubmitter(byte[] creator) {
    byte delim = 0x12; // A delimiter that occurs in the array after the MSPID String
    int offset = 2; // The index of the first character of the MSPID String
    int idx = ArrayUtils.indexOf(creator, delim); // Safe if array is null
    if (idx == ArrayUtils.INDEX_NOT_FOUND)
      return null;
    return new String(Arrays.copyOfRange(creator, offset, idx));
  }
```

Just in case anyone find this later and wants to know the answer, I found another way which will work better. 

```
  public static String getSubmitterId(byte[] creator) {
    Identities.SerializedIdentity id = getSerializedIdentity(creator);
    String subId = null;
    if (id != null)
      subId = id.getMspid();
    return subId;
  }
